======================================================================
KEY: dim(Omega_2) = |TT| = C(n,3) - 2*c_3
======================================================================
Formula verification:
  |TT| = C(n,3) - c_3
  |NT| = 3 * c_3
  |A_2| = C(n,3) + 2*c_3

  Verified |TT| = C(n,3)-c_3 and |NT| = 3*c_3 for 100 n=5 tournaments

  If dim(Omega_2) = |TT|, then |A_2| - J_2 = |TT| = C(n,3) - c_3
  So J_2 = |A_2| - |TT| = (C(n,3) + 2*c_3) - (C(n,3) - c_3) = 3*c_3 = |NT|
  This means EVERY NT path is individually constrained (A^2[a,c] = 1 always?)
  OR: the constraints kill exactly as many dimensions as there are NT paths

Verifying J_2 = 3*c_3 at n=5:
  MISMATCH: bits=4, J2=5, 3*c3=6

